cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on streaming media delivery and cache hierarchies in the network. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper discusses Dynamic Adaptive Streaming (DAS) and Quality of Experience (QoE) in video streaming. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper proposes a distributed cache placement scheme. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch on security concerns related to caching and streaming. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also less likely but possible as the paper may discuss how caching and streaming affect social networks and information dissemination.
